1
00:00:01,133 --> 00:00:03,033
<i>That means Dad just
got dragged into this mess?</i>

2
00:00:03,033 --> 00:00:05,267
<i>So, how did he get involved
in RoI's obsession?</i>

3
00:00:05,267 --> 00:00:07,267
<i> If Roy really is the killer,</i>

4
00:00:07,267 --> 00:00:10,433
<i>then that means Dad and
Uncle Fred's friendship is real.</i>

5
00:00:10,433 --> 00:00:13,033
<i>See? I told you
I was a good boy.</i>

6
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:15,100
<i>- Get out!
- It's payback time.</i>

7
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:16,633
<i> Mom, wait! Mom! Mom!</i>

8
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:18,567
<i>- Mom! You're not leaving.
- No.</i>

9
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:20,167
<i>- It's dangerous!
- Let me go!</i>

10
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:22,500
<i> I have to find my daughter!</i>

11
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:23,900
<i>- No, no, no, no, no...
- I have to find Jade!</i>

12
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:27,533
<i> Can you just shut up?  I'm
</i>getting  anxious because of you!

13
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:29,333
Hey! Don't yell at me like that.

14
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:32,067
- [SCREAMING]<i> Ah!
</i>- Hey!

15
00:00:32,067 --> 00:00:33,433
<i> Who did you go to?</i>

16
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:35,700
<i>Sari's grandfather,
who happens to be a...</i>

17
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,500
<i>- Fortune Teller.
- What did he say?</i>

18
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:39,533
<i> There is an abandoned...</i>

19
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:41,400
<i> house...</i>

20
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:42,733
<i> in the island...</i>

21
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:46,767
<i> nestled between two palm trees</i>

22
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:49,467
Jade's life is still in danger!

23
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:51,200
<i> I have some good news.</i>

24
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:55,233
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

25
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:59,700
[MARINA] Take a good look at
the back, side, and front.

26
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:01,700
- Sir Henri.
- Oh?

27
00:01:02,733 --> 00:01:05,067
Sir Henri, is there
any news on Jade?

28
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:08,133
This is the car Roi used.

29
00:01:08,167 --> 00:01:11,067
He could have hidden
in one of the islands here.

30
00:01:11,067 --> 00:01:12,667
That's where he probably
took your sister.

31
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:14,333
We're also checking this area.

32
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:16,800
There might be witnesses
who saw them.

33
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:18,367
We'll come with you.

34
00:01:18,367 --> 00:01:19,600
Whether it's here on
on another island

35
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:21,200
I'll look for Roi myself.

36
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:23,300
You can't come with us,
we might run into trouble.

37
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:25,100
[EDWARD] But what about Jade?

38
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:26,833
Don't worry about it, okay?

39
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:29,300
You'll be the first to see her
when we bring her back.

40
00:01:30,667 --> 00:01:32,600
Leave it to us, okay?

41
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:39,600
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

42
00:01:46,133 --> 00:01:53,067
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:02:45,633 --> 00:02:52,333
- [FIRE CRACKLING]
- [POTS CLATTERING]

44
00:02:52,367 --> 00:02:59,600
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

45
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:04,333
[ROI] You should eat.

46
00:03:05,567 --> 00:03:08,733
I don't want Frida to get mad
at me because I starved you.

47
00:03:13,367 --> 00:03:14,867
You're sick.

48
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:17,900
You're sick in the head.

49
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:22,500
You are brave, Jade.

50
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,167
You got that from your mother.

51
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,933
That's why I'm slowly
starting to like you.

52
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:34,167
[ROI] Your personality.

53
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,933
You're just like your mother.

54
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:41,567
Don't compare me to her.

55
00:03:41,567 --> 00:03:46,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

56
00:03:46,633 --> 00:03:48,300
That's what you think.

57
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:51,633
Eat.

58
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:53,867
I'll feed you.

59
00:03:54,700 --> 00:04:01,867
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:04:04,967 --> 00:04:07,233
- Go ahead and starve then!
- [PLATES CLATTERING]

61
00:04:15,367 --> 00:04:18,367
Can you get us something
to drink, please?

62
00:04:18,367 --> 00:04:20,400
Has there been an update
on Jade's whereabouts?

63
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:23,567
- What did the police say?
- They haven't found her yet.

64
00:04:23,567 --> 00:04:25,933
[MARTIN] What about Leon?

65
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:29,833
Leon went with Justin to see
where they found Roi's car.

66
00:04:29,867 --> 00:04:31,733
So they found it?
Where's Jade?

67
00:04:33,567 --> 00:04:35,367
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:36,900
Why don't we go there too?

69
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:38,833
Let's just go.

70
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:40,767
[SIGHS] Alright.

71
00:04:40,767 --> 00:04:43,500
- Luna, we'll follow them.
- [FRIDA] No, don't.

72
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:46,700
Don't go. They're asking
us to stay here.

73
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:47,700
Leon will...

74
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:49,700
Leon will contact us if ever.

75
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:53,333
Let's just stay here, Kiko.

76
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:55,367
We don't know if Roi
has any accomplices.

77
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:57,767
[GIO] If someone does go here...

78
00:04:59,467 --> 00:05:01,033
it would be better if
someone's with them.

79
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:04,933
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:05:04,933 --> 00:05:06,767
- Luna...
- Ma.

81
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:10,033
I hope Jade is okay.

82
00:05:10,033 --> 00:05:12,367
I really want her to come home.

83
00:05:12,367 --> 00:05:14,633
She is, Ma. She's okay.

84
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:16,467
Jade will come home,
don't worry.

85
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:19,800
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

86
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,400
[SIGHS]

87
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,967
Were you aware that my parents
have been separated for ages?

88
00:05:29,967 --> 00:05:32,767
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

89
00:05:32,767 --> 00:05:35,500
You were always
with my dad, right?

90
00:05:35,533 --> 00:05:37,067
I'm sure you know that.

91
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:41,400
[JADE] That they were cold
to each other.

92
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:44,033
Why are you telling me this?

93
00:05:45,467 --> 00:05:47,533
Mom wanted to leave him
for a long time now.

94
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:52,867
She wanted to leave.

95
00:05:53,933 --> 00:05:55,633
To live her own life.

96
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,767
She doesn't seem
to be happy anymore.

97
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:05,600
She wanted to leave so badly

98
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:06,800
that she didn't tell us

99
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,800
that she was planning
to move to a different country.

100
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,467
Did you know about that, too?

101
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:14,633
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

102
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:16,000
Where?

103
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,600
Which country?

104
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,633
Her residency has been approved.

105
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:24,067
I'm asking you where?!

106
00:06:24,067 --> 00:06:27,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

107
00:06:27,667 --> 00:06:29,933
She told us we were
already grown-ups

108
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:31,900
and that she would rather leave.

109
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:35,067
Because she feels so alone.

110
00:06:35,067 --> 00:06:40,733
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

111
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:42,033
No.

112
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:44,833
She's not leaving.

113
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:47,467
- [THUDS]
- No one is leaving!

114
00:06:47,467 --> 00:06:50,433
Because I never once
left her alone!

115
00:06:50,433 --> 00:06:52,767
I don't want her
to leave, either, Roi.

116
00:06:52,767 --> 00:06:54,600
So please...

117
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,600
I have to stop her.

118
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,733
Please, bring me to her Roi.

119
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:02,700
I just need to talk to her.

120
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:09,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

121
00:07:12,233 --> 00:07:13,733
[UTENSILS CLINKING]

122
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:15,800
- Have some drinks, boys.
- I'll carry it, Auntie.

123
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:18,133
Let me. I need a distraction.

124
00:07:18,133 --> 00:07:19,300
[EXHALES DEEPLY] Okay.

125
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,167
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

126
00:07:22,167 --> 00:07:23,400
[FRIDA] You're welcome.

127
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:30,367
I keep thinking Roi might
be hurting Jade.

128
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:33,833
Mom, let's stay positive.
Jade will be safe.

129
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:37,233
You need a distraction, Auntie?

130
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:41,867
How about you tell us
how you met Papa?

131
00:07:42,367 --> 00:07:44,833
Kiko, don't ask her that.

132
00:07:45,233 --> 00:07:46,400
[FRIDA] It's okay.

133
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:48,767
Maybe it's time you know too.

134
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:51,233
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:52,767
Um...

136
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:58,333
Michael and Fred were already
friends when I met them.

137
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:04,067
They both studied business,
but they loved archaeology.

138
00:08:04,067 --> 00:08:08,133
They loved antiques
and treasures.

139
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:15,500
[LUNA] Mom, I remember you said
Uncle Mike was your first crush.

140
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:17,167
- Yes.
- Because he was fun

141
00:08:17,167 --> 00:08:18,500
and adventurous.

142
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,967
Yes, that's true. But...

143
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,433
your dad was the one
who pursued me.

144
00:08:23,433 --> 00:08:25,267
And I appreciated him.

145
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:29,167
I appreciated everything
he did for me,

146
00:08:29,167 --> 00:08:32,933
so we became a couple
and eventually got married.

147
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:38,467
I loved your dad.

148
00:08:38,467 --> 00:08:43,400
Over time, however, we
had a lot of disagreements.

149
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:46,233
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:08:46,233 --> 00:08:49,033
But Mom, you never
showed us that.

151
00:08:49,033 --> 00:08:54,300
[FRIDA] Yes, Luna. If there's
one thing we both agreed on,

152
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:57,200
it's that we love our children.

153
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:59,533
We didn't want you caught up
in our problems.

154
00:08:59,533 --> 00:09:03,833
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

155
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:05,100
But Michael...

156
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:10,433
He was there to listen
whenever I was sad

157
00:09:11,267 --> 00:09:13,567
and frustrated because of Fred.

158
00:09:15,233 --> 00:09:20,933
That's why I started to feel
that way about him again.

159
00:09:20,933 --> 00:09:25,467
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

160
00:09:25,467 --> 00:09:27,867
I'm sorry. I shouldn't
be telling you this.

161
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:30,433
But your father and I
didn't have an affair.

162
00:09:34,367 --> 00:09:35,967
You don't need to explain.

163
00:09:37,233 --> 00:09:39,967
[FRIDA] Mike was
a very caring person.

164
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:44,600
And I had feelings for him,
but he only saw me as a friend.

165
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,900
[FRIDA SOBS]

166
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:52,433
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

167
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:56,000
[MICHAEL]
<i> I'm your friend, Frida.</i>

168
00:09:57,533 --> 00:09:59,367
<i> Frederico's also my friend.</i>

169
00:10:02,167 --> 00:10:04,267
[FRIDA] Fred didn't believe it.

170
00:10:04,267 --> 00:10:06,000
But heaven knows

171
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:11,367
that he was just a good friend.

172
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:18,433
But he eventually
came to believe Papa.

173
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,067
I hope so.

174
00:10:24,533 --> 00:10:25,600
I hope so.

175
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:30,000
Thank you for being honest.

176
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:34,567
You didn't have to do that
for Kiko, but you did.

177
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:41,567
It's up to you, Martin,
if you want to believe me.

178
00:10:42,167 --> 00:10:45,433
But as Michael's sons,

179
00:10:45,433 --> 00:10:50,267
I want you to know
that he was a good person

180
00:10:50,267 --> 00:10:52,633
and that he was
good to my family.

181
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,967
He shouldn't have died.

182
00:10:57,367 --> 00:11:04,233
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:10,100
Please, Roi.

184
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,600
I need to talk to Mom.

185
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:15,300
I have to stop her
before it's too late.

186
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:17,700
Please, Roi.

187
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:20,700
I thought you loved her.

188
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:25,167
- Why don't you just let me--
- Shut up!

189
00:11:25,667 --> 00:11:27,533
You're getting
on my nerves, girl!

190
00:11:29,633 --> 00:11:31,000
Be quiet.

191
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:36,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

192
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:37,400
[CLANGING]

193
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:46,033
[SOBS, BREATHES HEAVILY]

194
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:57,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

195
00:11:59,133 --> 00:12:00,567
[PHONE KEYPAD BEEPING]

196
00:12:01,367 --> 00:12:05,433
[LINE RINGING]

197
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:10,633
[PHONE RINGING]

198
00:12:10,633 --> 00:12:11,633
Hello?

199
00:12:12,333 --> 00:12:13,200
Roi?

200
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:15,000
[FRIDA] Roi?

201
00:12:15,533 --> 00:12:17,267
<i> Please say something.</i>

202
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:20,033
I know you, right?

203
00:12:20,033 --> 00:12:21,133
[WHISPERS] Mom...

204
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:24,533
Where's Jade?
Where's my daughter, Roi?

205
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:25,600
[WHISPERING] Mom...

206
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,600
<i> Roi?</i>

207
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:33,167
I wish you hadn't taken Jade.

208
00:12:33,167 --> 00:12:35,100
I wish you had just
talked to me instead.

209
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:38,067
We would've been
together by now.

210
00:12:38,067 --> 00:12:38,800
Mom--

211
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:42,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:12:42,167 --> 00:12:43,300
Roi, you know,

213
00:12:44,033 --> 00:12:46,167
the flowers you gave me...

214
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,133
<i> I loved them so much.</i>

215
00:12:49,533 --> 00:12:52,233
<i> But I had to throw them away
in front of my kids</i>

216
00:12:52,233 --> 00:12:54,167
<i>because I didn't want them
to know.</i>

217
00:12:54,167 --> 00:12:55,267
But now...

218
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:58,667
why would I need
to keep pretending?

219
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:02,733
I thought maybe we
should be together now.

220
00:13:03,467 --> 00:13:06,700
Just let Jade go.

221
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:09,467
<i>Take me instead.
Let's go somewhere far away.</i>

222
00:13:09,467 --> 00:13:11,733
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

223
00:13:11,733 --> 00:13:13,400
You're just saying that, Frida.

224
00:13:14,367 --> 00:13:15,367
I'm not stupid.

225
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:21,067
You know, Roi,
before Fred died,

226
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,100
I really wanted to leave.

227
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,733
<i> I wish you had just told me
so I'd know.</i>

228
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:30,867
<i>Because I really didn't
want to be alone.</i>

229
00:13:30,867 --> 00:13:34,100
<i> I'd rather be with you.</i>

230
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:35,700
<i> Because...</i>

231
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:39,300
who was always there
when I was sad?

232
00:13:40,667 --> 00:13:42,533
Who was always there for me?

233
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:45,433
Isn't it you, Roi?

234
00:13:46,433 --> 00:13:47,833
[SNIFFLES]

235
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:51,367
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

236
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:52,500
Fine.

237
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:55,500
<i>You're really the one I need
anyway.</i>

238
00:13:58,233 --> 00:14:00,167
I'll send you the location
where we'll meet.

239
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,800
[WHISPERING] No, Mom. Mom. Mom.

240
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,000
Okay.

241
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:08,467
B-But what about Jade?
Where's my daughter?

242
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:10,367
<i> But, Frida...</i>

243
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:13,233
You better not fool me...

244
00:14:14,733 --> 00:14:16,300
or I'll kill your daughter.

245
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:19,700
- [LINE DISCONNECTING]
- Roi.

246
00:14:20,433 --> 00:14:21,333
Roi!

247
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:22,867
- [LUNA] Ma.
- Roi.

248
00:14:22,867 --> 00:14:24,467
Mom, what are you doing?

249
00:14:24,467 --> 00:14:26,600
I'm saving my daughter!

250
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:32,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

251
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:35,500
You shouldn't have put
yourself in danger, Mom!

252
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,033
If I hadn't done that,

253
00:14:37,033 --> 00:14:39,067
we wouldn't be able
to track Jade!

254
00:14:39,067 --> 00:14:42,433
But what if Roi
doesn't keep his word, huh?

255
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:44,133
What if he takes
both you and Jade?

256
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:46,700
That's why we should be there.

257
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:48,833
You can't go there alone,
Mrs. Almazan.

258
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:49,833
He'll kill my daughter

259
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:52,133
if he finds out
there are police involved.

260
00:14:52,133 --> 00:14:54,067
That's why we need
to plan this carefully.

261
00:14:54,067 --> 00:14:55,967
- [FRIDA EXHALES]
- When are you meeting?

262
00:14:57,967 --> 00:14:58,967
[SIGHS]

263
00:14:59,667 --> 00:15:00,867
He messaged me.

264
00:15:00,867 --> 00:15:02,600
[EXHALES] He said it's later.

265
00:15:03,233 --> 00:15:10,167
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

266
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:12,167
I'm coming with you.

267
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:14,000
I'm coming too!

268
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,100
[LEON] No, Justin.

269
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:17,433
Luna needs someone
with her here.

270
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:20,833
I'll talk to the team first.

271
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:26,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:15:26,867 --> 00:15:28,967
We already lost your father.

273
00:15:29,667 --> 00:15:32,433
We can't lose another
member of this family.

274
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:34,667
That's why I'll do everything

275
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,700
just to bring your sister home.

276
00:15:37,533 --> 00:15:38,700
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

277
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:39,800
Jade.

278
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:46,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

279
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:56,933
[JADE EXHALES]

280
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:00,733
[ROI] I should have told Frida
right away how I felt.

281
00:16:00,733 --> 00:16:03,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

282
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:05,767
Maybe it wouldn't
have come to this.

283
00:16:08,900 --> 00:16:10,033
Look...

284
00:16:12,133 --> 00:16:13,967
[BREATH QUIVERS]

285
00:16:13,967 --> 00:16:15,500
You even got hurt.

286
00:16:16,133 --> 00:16:23,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

287
00:16:23,033 --> 00:16:24,667
You'll be free soon, Jade...

288
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,067
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

289
00:16:26,067 --> 00:16:27,900
Once I meet your mother.

290
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:34,600
But you won't be able
to be with her anymore.

291
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:38,800
Because I'll take her away
from all of you.

292
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:40,933
[WHIMPERS]

293
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:43,533
Anyway...

294
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:47,833
[SOBS QUIETLY]

295
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:49,300
I'm the only one
she wants to be with.

296
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,667
[BREATH QUIVERS]

297
00:16:51,867 --> 00:16:58,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

298
00:16:58,833 --> 00:17:00,000
Do you want to say something?

299
00:17:04,967 --> 00:17:06,800
Don't hurt my mother.

300
00:17:07,967 --> 00:17:09,600
Please.

301
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:19,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

302
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:20,833
Come on, Jade.

303
00:17:22,233 --> 00:17:23,833
I'm not going to hurt her.

304
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,000
[BREATH QUIVERS]

305
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:29,767
- I'll love her...
- [JADE EXHALES DEEPLY]

306
00:17:29,767 --> 00:17:31,833
...every single day.

307
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,167
[JADE WHIMPERS]

308
00:17:37,933 --> 00:17:44,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

309
00:17:55,167 --> 00:17:57,133
[LUNA] Mom, Leon,
please be careful.

310
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,300
Wait!

311
00:18:04,067 --> 00:18:05,400
I'm coming with you.

312
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:06,833
You can't, Edward.

313
00:18:07,633 --> 00:18:10,733
You might just get hurt.
Your father will worry.

314
00:18:10,733 --> 00:18:12,633
Auntie, you can't stop me.

315
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:13,967
Jade's life is already
in danger,

316
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:15,633
so just choose.

317
00:18:15,633 --> 00:18:18,067
Are you taking me with you,
or should I just follow you?

318
00:18:18,633 --> 00:18:20,033
[FRIDA] But what about Andy?

319
00:18:20,633 --> 00:18:22,100
Auntie, I'm old enough.

320
00:18:22,133 --> 00:18:23,667
I can decide for myself.

321
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,400
And this isn't
Dad's decision anymore.

322
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:29,333
I'll handle it, Mom.

323
00:18:31,700 --> 00:18:33,100
Okay, fine.

324
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:34,300
Let's go.

325
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:42,033
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

326
00:18:46,633 --> 00:18:48,200
[MARTIN EXHALES DEEPLY]
Okay, bro. Be careful.

327
00:18:49,767 --> 00:18:51,200
[KIKO] What did he say?
Have they found Jade?

328
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:53,800
Not yet. But they know
where she is now.

329
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:54,733
Where?

330
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:56,233
Let's go there.
They might need help.

331
00:18:56,267 --> 00:18:57,667
[MARTIN] He didn't say.

332
00:18:57,667 --> 00:18:59,033
The police said
it's confidential.

333
00:18:59,033 --> 00:19:00,300
What if we follow them?

334
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:02,733
Kiko, we can't.

335
00:19:02,733 --> 00:19:04,000
It's a sensitive operation.

336
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,967
Let's let the police handle it
so Jade can get home safely.

337
00:19:06,967 --> 00:19:08,333
So we'll just wait here?

338
00:19:08,333 --> 00:19:10,267
Isn't it harder just
sitting around like this?

339
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:17,167
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

340
00:19:20,267 --> 00:19:24,133
[JADE SOBS, SNIFFLES]

341
00:19:24,133 --> 00:19:25,600
Don't cry, Jade.

342
00:19:27,267 --> 00:19:28,833
Frida might get mad at me.

343
00:19:30,767 --> 00:19:34,867
You should look okay
when she sees you.

344
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:39,233
So she won't feel sorry for you.

345
00:19:41,933 --> 00:19:43,900
I don't want my love
to be sad.

346
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:47,733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

347
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:49,233
That's what I call her.

348
00:19:51,667 --> 00:19:52,767
"My love."

349
00:19:55,733 --> 00:19:57,800
Because I love her so much.

350
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:00,633
[JADE SOBS]

351
00:20:01,967 --> 00:20:05,200
I'm already thinking
about where we'll go...

352
00:20:06,167 --> 00:20:07,433
...where I'll take her.

353
00:20:09,367 --> 00:20:11,733
I've saved up a bit.

354
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:18,367
We can finally leave
this island.

355
00:20:20,233 --> 00:20:23,200
[JADE SOBBING]

356
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:29,067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

357
00:20:29,067 --> 00:20:30,700
But don't be sad, Jade.

358
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,767
I'll let her call you.

359
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,433
But only occasionally.

360
00:20:41,267 --> 00:20:46,800
Of course, we'll be busy
with our new life.

361
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:51,500
Shh. There, there.

362
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:58,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

363
00:21:16,533 --> 00:21:17,900
Come on.

364
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:22,500
So you can say goodbye
to my love properly.

365
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:29,300
[UNSETTLING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

366
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:39,800
Leon, please...

367
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:41,900
Leave now.
Roi might see you.

368
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:43,767
- Mom...
- [SIGHS]

369
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:46,800
Leon, promise me.

370
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:49,900
No matter what happens,
Jade is the priority.

371
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:51,933
- But--
- No, no, no, look.

372
00:21:51,933 --> 00:21:53,000
[FRIDA] Leon, listen to me.

373
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,700
No matter what happens,
Jade is the priority.

374
00:21:58,733 --> 00:21:59,900
[EXHALES]

375
00:22:00,933 --> 00:22:03,000
[SNIFFLES, EXHALES]

376
00:22:06,067 --> 00:22:07,733
Be careful.

377
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,633
I love you so much.

378
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,133
[FRIDA WHIMPERS]

379
00:22:15,767 --> 00:22:17,567
Go, go, go, go!

380
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:18,700
Mom.

381
00:22:18,700 --> 00:22:19,800
Leon.

382
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:25,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

383
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:26,567
Go.

384
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,667
[SIGHS]

385
00:22:33,933 --> 00:22:35,767
<i>Run, okay?
I'm the only one Bok is after.</i>

386
00:22:35,767 --> 00:22:36,900
<i> We're not leaving you.</i>

387
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:37,967
<i> We're staying together!</i>

388
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:41,700
<i> One... Two... Three... Run!</i>

389
00:22:42,133 --> 00:22:44,433
<i>- Chase them!
- [GUNSHOTS]</i>

390
00:22:45,467 --> 00:22:46,833
- [FRIDA SCREAMS]
- [GRUNTS]

391
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:48,000
<i>- There he is!
- [GROANS IN PAIN]</i>

392
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,467
[FRIDA SCREAMS]

393
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:50,667
<i> Leon!</i>

394
00:22:50,667 --> 00:22:52,267
[GRUNTS]

395
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:53,733
- [THUDS]
- [GROANS]

396
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:56,733
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- [GRUNTING, GROANING]

397
00:22:56,733 --> 00:22:58,733
<i> Jade! Jade!</i>

398
00:22:58,733 --> 00:22:59,800
<i>- Like what happened to Jade--
- Shh!</i>

399
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:01,700
<i>No! As long as they
haven't said anything,</i>

400
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:04,067
<i>nothing bad has happened
to our sister.</i>

401
00:23:04,067 --> 00:23:05,867
[BLOWS LANDING]

402
00:23:05,867 --> 00:23:08,267
<i> Just take care of them, okay?</i>

403
00:23:08,267 --> 00:23:09,633
<i> Go now, son.</i>

404
00:23:11,033 --> 00:23:12,467
- [BLOW LANDS]
- That's enough!

405
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:15,133
<i>- Gio!
- [GUNSHOTS]</i>

406
00:23:15,133 --> 00:23:18,000
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

407
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,533
<i>I won't be asking you
for money anymore, Gio.</i>

